                            <comment id="13658657" author="dlyubimov" created="Wed, 15 May 2013 19:44:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you sure? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;any job will fail if output directory exists, unless -ow is specified. FWIW i don&apos;t recollect any troubles running it over and over as long as i give it -ow (same as with other CLIs)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13658667" author="smarthi" created="Wed, 15 May 2013 19:57:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It does fail if the output directory already exists, and that&apos;s fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But it does not clear --tempDir when -ow is specified, the user has to manually clean the tempDir before each run else the Q-job, Bt-Job, U-job etc.. fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally the tempDir should be cleared up when SSVDcli exits - &lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  fs.deleteOnexit(getTempPath())
  &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;unless there are other reasons for not doing it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was proposing to clear the --tempDir along with outputDir if -ow is specified,  and to always delete the tempDir when the job exits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similar issue with the RowSimilarity job was fixed as part of Mahout-834.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
